{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-template-excerpt-js","path":"/excerpts/nature_spring_equinox/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Darkness loses its upper hand,<br>\nBalance has at last been regained,<br>\nThe sun is bright but the wind is cold,<br>\nOld man winter's reign is to end,<br>\nFlowers are appearing again,<br>\nThe change seems as though it's god sent,<br>\nThose long dark nights are almost gone,<br>\nSummer days shall dawn before long,<br>\nCrystal blue poised against the dark,<br>\nLight's lighter and dark is nicer,<br>\nAn evening out of power,<br>\nThe days now slowly grow longer,<br>\nA change cannot come soon enough,<br>\nSpring's equinox brings us relief,<br>\nBalance rests on the edge of a knife,<br>\nNature has been given new life.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"January 20, 2020","title":"Spring Equinox","audio":{"publicURL":"/static/15e5b7fcc971578433f6023359415a74/Christian Lacdael - Nature - 20 Spring Equinox.mp3"},"icon":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1,"src":"/static/422c35d300e436694406bfd22bda0cec/7d509/poem%20spring%20equinox.jpg","srcSet":"/static/422c35d300e436694406bfd22bda0cec/f836f/poem%20spring%20equinox.jpg 200w,\n/static/422c35d300e436694406bfd22bda0cec/2244e/poem%20spring%20equinox.jpg 400w,\n/static/422c35d300e436694406bfd22bda0cec/7d509/poem%20spring%20equinox.jpg 720w","sizes":"(max-width: 720px) 100vw, 720px"}}}}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/excerpts/nature_spring_equinox/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3649515864"]}